Brad Scott is coming to GOE March 12, 13, &amp; 14 at the Embassy
Suites Conference Center in East Peoria, IL (<a href="maps/1.php" rel="facebox">map</a>).
Author and Bible teacher Brad Scott has been teaching the Bible since
1971 and has authored several books. 
Brad's extensive Hebraic knowledge, his lively speaking style, and his
wonderful sense of humor all blend together to make this man a very
popular speaker at conferences, churches, and Messianic congregations. 
&nbsp; <br>(See Brad's Web site at<span class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><a
href="http://www.wildbranch.org" target="_blank"
style="color: rgb(17, 65, 112);">www.wildbranch.org</a>.)
<br>Brad will be speaking at 7 p.m. March 12
&amp; 13, and at 2 p.m. March 14 at Embassy Suites Conference Center,
100 Conference Center Dr., East Peoria.
Free admission.&nbsp; An offering will be taken.
Brad will also be attending our regular Sabbath meeting at the
Methodist Church that Saturday morning at 11 a.m.
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; 
If you are coming from out of town and need
to spend the night in Peoria, MAKE RESERVATIONS FOR A MOTEL ROOM AS
SOON AS POSSIBLE. "March Madness" (the Illinois State High School
Basketball Tournament)
is in Peoria that same weekend, so MOTELS WILL BE FILLED. To reserve a
room at the Embassy Suites Hotel, phone 1-800-EMBASSY. There are
cheaper motels just one-half mile from the Conference Center
(all Phone numbers are 309 area code):&nbsp;
In East Peoria: Motel 6, 699-7281; Fairfield
Inn, 699-4100; Holiday Inn Express, 694-4959; Super 8, 698-8889. About
2 miles away: Hampton Inn, 694-0711; Stoney Creek Inn, 694-1300. In
Peoria, about 1 mile away: Staybridge Suites, 673-7829. </span></span>
